DataElement.preferredName: Brief Pain Inventory Questionnaire Last Week Pain at its Worst Score 11 Point Scale
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A person's stated observation rating pain at its worst in the last week, using a 11 point Likert scale.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Brief Pain Inventory Questionnaire Last Week Pain at its Worst Score
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A standardized survey originally developed and copyrighted by Charles S. Cleeland in 1991 which is used to evaluate the severity of a patient's pain and the impact that their pain has on their daily activities. This longer version is more clinically useful, can be completed by the patient or in an interview format and consists of 32 multi-level questions covering areas such as location, type, and severity of pain as well as the use of pain medications._The most recent week, including today._A question about an individual's pain at its worst._A number or range of numeric values measuring performance, function, quality, or ability.
